title: Baudelaire fleurs fra eng with sartre/benjamin
description:
My study fiel is the economy and i am too stupid to understand poetry , nevertheless

my best friend in the university had this book as his personal bible. 20 years have 

passed and i have not had the time to read the best poetry book of the aristocratic 

century of european history. Anyway , this is a bit common here in spain: i will read 

it "tomorrow" ,and better if you can do it for me (french books are always dangerous)






-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The files are:


1   the original french edition 1856 LES FLEURS DU MAL (bad scans but a treasure)
2   a modern edition in french
3   a modern edition in english

4   some remarks on the issue by Walter Benjamin
5   a book written by sartre with more stuff around
